{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"alias":"lanky-turret-worry","description":"## Why\n\nEpic A shipped a basic batch-criteria editor where the user TYPES prompt-ids and overlay\npredicates as free text — error-prone and undiscoverable. The plan-review migration (B2) makes the\nbatch's criteria list the primary thing a human edits, so the editor must let the user SELECT\ncriteria, prompts, and overlay triggers from lists and CREATE new ones, not hand-type ids/expressions.\n\n## What\n\nUpgrade the workflow visual editor's batch step (and prompt/agent steps) so editing is selection-\nand form-driven, for both CRITERIA and PROMPTS:\n\n- **Criterion / prompt fields → dropdowns** sourced from the library enumerate API (B-DM), each\n  option showing its description (no free-text id typing).\n- **Overlay trigger (`when`) → dropdown** of THIS workflow's available triggers (the\n  `overlay_triggers` step's keyword + structural outputs), rendered as the correct\n  `${{ steps.<triggers>.outputs.<name> }}` expression, plus an \"(always include)\" option.\n- **Create new overlay trigger** — inline: adds a `{name: [keywords]}` entry to the\n  `overlay_triggers` step config; it then appears in the dropdown.\n- **Create new criterion / prompt — full in-editor authoring**: a form to enter the name + rubric/\n  body; on save the editor calls the B-DM write API to create the prompt-library `.md` + regen the\n  index, and references the new id in the step. Must keep the prompt-drift CI gate green.\n\n## Scope\n\n- Editor front-end (`editor_assets/src/`) changes: replace the text fields with library-backed\n  selects + the authoring form; inject the enumerate data + per-workflow trigger list.\n- A small editor-server endpoint to invoke the B-DM create/update API (the editor writes files via\n  the server, not the browser).\n- Real-browser E2E (Playwright) covering: pick-existing criterion/prompt, pick + create overlay\n  trigger, author a new criterion/prompt end-to-end, and persistence to the IR + library.\n- Depends on B-DM (the library write/enumerate data model) and the v3 batch schema (on main).\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] The batch step's criterion/prompt fields are dropdowns sourced from the library (with\n      descriptions); the overlay `when` is a dropdown of the workflow's overlay-trigger outputs + \"(always)\".\n- [ ] A user can create a new overlay trigger inline (adds it to the `overlay_triggers` step) and\n      immediately select it.\n- [ ] A user can author a new criterion AND a new prompt in-editor (name + rubric/body); on save it\n      is written to the library via the B-DM API, the index is regenerated, and the new id is referenced\n      in the step.\n- [ ] A real-browser E2E proves pick-existing, create-trigger, and author-new-criterion/prompt end\n      to end with persistence to the IR + library; the prompt-drift gate stays green.\n- [ ] `make lint` + the full test suite pass.","id":"92fa-6657-3579-4043","parent_id":"72d5-79ec-9e2e-4a2b","priority":2,"tags":[],"ticket_type":"story","title":"B-UX: Visual editor — select/create criteria, prompts & overlay triggers (pickers + in-editor authoring)"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1782436649251142001,"uuid":"5af8f9dd-2226-4d46-8cf8-7413c7d9bf1d"}